of education. Just because someone has a different primary language does not mean that they don’t deserve an equal education to others. According to the World Federation of the Deaf, 80%25 of the deaf community don’t get an education due to their ability to attend regular schools that teach in spoken languages[2]. Some solutions to this problem involve having teachers trained in sign language and ensuring that students from the deaf community don’t feel singled out while still maintaining their connection to that community. It’s important to remember that sign language is an important method of communication for the deaf community and that resources should accommodate those who use it. %0a%3c %0a%3c [1] “Sign Language Key to Deaf People’s Rights.” Human Rights Watch, 28 Oct. 2020, www.hrw.org/news/2018/09/23/sign-language-key-deaf-peoples-rights.%0a%3c %0a%3c [2]“Human Rights of the Deaf.” WFD, 11 Aug. 2017, wfdeaf.org/our-work/human-rights-of-the-deaf.%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Expansions:%0a%3c [[#expansions]]%0a%3c %0a%3c [[#expansionsend]]%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c %25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%3c %0a%3c (:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%3c %0a%3c You must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%3c %0a%3c (:else:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%3c %0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c ----%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Comments%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c ----%0a%3c (:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a%3c !!Change article category%0a%3c (:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c (:Section: A:)%0a%3c (:Category: SignLanguage:)%0a%3c (:Title: Discrimination Related to Sign Language:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
